cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for the classification of different stages of malaria using limited labelled data size. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of pre-trained convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and comparison with other well-known CNNs also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The study also involves the use of multi-wavelength to increase the sample size, which can be related to the data science (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the automated classification of malaria-infected stages, which can be related to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
